* G1 (overall score, without academic outcome) correlates with E1 ( without the Interdisciplinarity variable <involvement of researchers from other areas>)

```{r echo=FALSE, fig.width=16}

# G1 (overall score, no acad) correlates with E1.transdisciplinarity (no interdisc)
g1e1.df3 <- as.data.frame(cbind(g1 = g1.modf_civil,
                                e1 = e1.df_trans))

g1e1.cor <- cor.test(g1e1.df3$g1, g1e1.df3$e1,  method="spearman")
g1e1.ann <- paste0("p = ",format(round(g1e1.cor$p.value, 2), nsmall = 2) , "   rho=",format(round(g1e1.cor$estimate, 2), nsmall = 2) )
anno1 = grobTree(textGrob(g1e1.ann, x = 0.63, y = 0.97, hjust = 0, gp = gpar(col = "#e7298a", fontsize = 11, fontface = "bold")))

g1e1.ann
ggplotly(
ggplot(g1e1.df3, 
       aes(x=e1, y=g1)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  ggtitle("") + 
  geom_smooth(method=lm, se=TRUE, fullrange=TRUE, color='#e7298a')+
  geom_jitter(color='#377eb8')+
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(1,20,1)) + 
  annotation_custom(anno1) +
  geom_point(color='#377eb8') +
  #scale_y_continuous(name = "UNC45A", limits = c(5,15), breaks = seq(5, 15, 2)) + 
  #theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), 
        #panel.background = element_blank(), 
  #      axis.line = element_line(color="black"), 
  #      axis.line.x = element_line(color="black")) 
  #theme_bw()
  labs(
    x="groupsInvolved",
    y = "impactTargetGroup")
)

```
